The 6 Division of the Nigerian Army, Port Harcourt, has warned its officers and soldiers to desist from escorting politicians during the Saturday’s elections. It also warned that soldiers were not allowed within the vicinity of polling units. The Commander of the Division of the Nigerian Army,  Major-General Jamil Sarham, gave the warning yesterday at a media briefing. He said anyone seen in military uniform in polling units will be treated as an imposter. Army denies killings, mass arrests of voters Army denies killings, mass arrest of voters during Rivers re-run election Rivers re-run: Army denies killings,mass arrest of voters